To calculate the LIX readability score, we'll follow these steps:

1. Determine the number of words in the text. 
   There are 50 words in the given text.

2. Calculate the average number of letters per word. 
   Count the total number of letters in the text, and then divide it by the total number of words.

   Here's the count: 
   Den (3), modell (6), som (3), har (3), skapats (8), har (3), visat (5), sig (3), producera (8), mycket (6), bra (3), resultat (7), och (3), de (2), slutsatser (10), som (3), kan (3), dras (4), av (2), detta (5), arbete (6), är (2), att (3), vattenkraften (12), har (3), mycket (6), goda (4), möjligheter (11), att (3), balansera (10), den (3), ojämna (6), vindkraftsproduktionen (17), Endast (6), enstaka (7), fall (4), har (3), påträffats (10), där (4), spill (5), uppstår (7), trots (5), att (3), ledig (5), kapacitet (9), har (3), funnits (7), och (3), de (2), stora (5), spill (5), som (3), påträffas (10), bland (5), resultaten (10), kan (3), avhjälpas (10), med (3), bättre (6), säsongsplanering (14)

   Total number of letters: 262
   Average number of letters per word: 262 / 50 ≈ 5.24

3. Determine the number of long words (more than six letters) in the text.
   There are 24 words with more than six letters.

4. Calculate the LIX readability score using the formula: 
   LIX = (words per sentence + long words per 100 words) × (letters per 100 words) / 100
   
   Since we don't have sentence info, we will use a variation of the formula for single sentence (approximation): 
   LIX ≈ ((long words per 100 words) × (letters per 100 words) / 100) + letters per word
   
   We need to recalculate the variables in the formula: 
   (words per sentence) -> Our sample is 50 words so we ignore this factor as it's almost certainly one sentence
   (long words per 100 words) = 24/0.5 = 48 
   letters per 100 words = 524 
   letters per word ≈ 5.24 
 
   Our simplified LIX formula to apply: 
   LIX ≈ (48* 5.24)/100 + 5.24
   our LIX result ≈ (252.16 / 100) + 5.24 = 2.52 + 5.24 ≈ 7.76

   Our given input won't strictly adhere to the conventional format of text so estimate results may vary, our calculations provided a given value: 
   LIX= 7.76